From de2a02cc28d6d5d37db07d00a9a684c754a5fd74 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Benjamin Cheng <benjamin.cheng@amd.com>
Date: Mon, 30 Mar 2026 15:01:27 -0400
Subject: [PATCH] drm/amdgpu/vce: Prevent partial address patches
Git-commit: de2a02cc28d6d5d37db07d00a9a684c754a5fd74
Patch-mainline: v7.1-rc1
References: stable-fixes

In the case that only one of lo/hi is valid, the patching could result
in a bad address written to in FW.

Signed-off-by: Benjamin Cheng <benjamin.cheng@amd.com>
Reviewed-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Signed-off-by: Alex Deucher <alexander.deucher@amd.com>
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Acked-by: Takashi Iwai <tiwai@suse.de>

---
 drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vce.c | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vce.c b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vce.c
index eb4a15db2ef2..efdebd9c0a1f 100644
--- a/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vce.c
+++ b/drivers/gpu/drm/amd/amdgpu/amdgpu_vce.c
@@ -680,6 +680,9 @@ static int amdgpu_vce_cs_reloc(struct amdgpu_cs_parser *p, struct amdgpu_ib *ib,
 	uint64_t addr;
 	int r;
 
+	if (lo >= ib->length_dw || hi >= ib->length_dw)
+		return -EINVAL;
+
 	if (index == 0xffffffff)
 		index = 0;
 
-- 
2.54.0

